metadata.name: LA BOUGIE üïØ #269
metadata.description:
This work is a collection along the lines of abstract works that I produced during the last year, and this is the first generative project in the form of a collaboration with the artist's friend Arash. This is the beginning of the production of fascinating works that we have been working on for several projects for months. In the background of this piece, there is a combination of Mondrian's known works with his well-known color palette and style, and the compositions try to remember Mondrian's works and create new and different designs. This deconstruction of The style Art movement continued and flourished with his other contemporary artists; Fx Hash's one-year candle combines de Stijl's work with a new pattern that creates new compositions independent of this work.

Unique collection by ArashMp and Chistai for #fxhashturnsone
Happy birthday fx(hash)!

metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes

And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: BWEEPS  #267
metadata.description:
A minimalist, black-and-white generative profile picture (PFP) created to commemorate one-year anniversary of Bwople project by Gengoya. The artwork is derived from an initial sketch of Bwople which, despite being not the one that was chosen, still managed to captivate interests. The project provides a unique glimpse into an alternate universe in which Bwople could have been represented.

All images are hand-drawn work by Gengoya and composed by Vector Recite using PureSpider's fxhash-pfp maker tool.

To download the full size image on fx(hash):
- Click "open" below the image
- Left click on the image, a "Download image" button will appear on the bottom right.
- Click the "Download image" button.

metadata.name: Clutch #169
metadata.description:
Halftones, dynamic composition and high color contrasts for a groovy composition inspired by action b-movies, their posters and music.

Semi-realtime javascript / webgl.
Desktop / Chrome recommended.

You can find more infos about the project in the fx(text) linked below.

Controls :
- Press [SPACE] to show/hide the user interface
- Mouse wheel/middle/ Pinch : Zoom
- After zooming, Mouse left / Drag : Pan

Keyboard shortcuts and additionnal instructions : 
- [R]eset the camera.
- Toggle the [F]rame.
- Unlock the [C]amera, with rotation on Mouse2.
- Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys [1] to [9] (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). I recommend starting with [4] and going from there. What is captured is what's on screen, so you can get creative if you so desire.

NFT License

metadata.name: Plottable Era: (I) Primitive #335
metadata.description:
'Plottable Era: (I) Primitive' is the first generator in the "Era" generators series, highlighting different periods and civilizations. This first series "Primitive" shows the beginning of mankind with people exploring the mountains and traveling on the sea during sunset.

The digital version simulates ink effects and adds a subtle animation over the water. Each outcome is also physically plottable with pens: A SVG file can be exported (right-click save) to plot the piece physically. The plots are designed to be executed in A4 format on either fountain pens (on white paper) or gel pens (Black / Blue).

Thanks to the utility token decoupling, you can get a physical version: the digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their own materials and ship to collectors ‚Äì as long as NFT is owned at request time.

More details and Source code: https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-era-primitive

@greweb ‚Äì 2022 ‚Äì tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM ‚Äì CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

reserve is set to previous 2022 physical plot collectors.

metadata.name: Enfantines II. Enfantillages Pittoresques #116
metadata.description:
The Enfantines¬†are three sets of beginner piano pieces by¬†Erik Satie, written with the aim of preparing children for the sound patterns of modern music. Composed in 1913, these are genuine children‚Äôs pieces, crafted for small hands, easy to learn. 

‚ÄúEnfantines II. Enfantillages Pittoresques‚Äù is the second of a set of algorithms that explore the basics of Generative Art, written with the aim of preparing artists for the script patterns of digital life. ‚ÄúEnfantillages Pittoresques‚Äù experiments with predefined plots, colour blending, webgl shaders, and generative music; all with a fresh, childish style. This algorithm has been trained to draw basic shapes in accordance to Satie‚Äôs lyrics. However, it uses them in unusual ways and creates what looks like fantastic creatures, microscopic beings, or, to follow Corneille, Constant, and Appel: "human animals".

‚ÄúIt took me four years to paint like Raphael, but a lifetime to paint like a child‚Äù Attributed to Picasso (falsely, probably)

With two modes that won‚Äôt produce the same outputs, ‚ÄúEnfantines‚Äù are best experienced twice. In music mode, the code uses Satie‚Äôs piano composition as a way of taming randomness, the sounds affecting the parameters of the strokes.

Hey, these have won me congratulations from the Shah of Persia and the King of Yvetot!


# INTERACTIVITY
Press M or Double Tap (mobile) for AUDIO mode
Wait for SILENT mode
Press I for Trait Info (desktop)
Press 1 for Canvas Save (desktop)

Introduce ‚Äú?pixelDensity=171‚Äù after URL for FULL SCREEN MODE (pseudo-deterministic).
Introduce ‚Äú?pixelDensity=X‚Äù for HQ renders (standard is 2, and 8 produces 400ppi 40x44cm prints).


# EASY-TO-READ CODE
The ‚ÄúEnfantines‚Äù are educational algorithms. The code has been compressed and minified for a performance boost, but can be read fully in GitHub: https://github.com/ratchitect/


# PERFORMANCE
Better experienced with Chrome.
